		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If Dwedit is making a renderer that must be scanline-based for performance reasons (e.g. the target platform's underlying video hardware is scanline-based, and the target platform's CPU is not fast enough for a full software PPU), then sampling fine X at x=8 and the rest at x=257 should work, right?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


