	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My emulator renders complete scanlines only and still handles Slalom correctly. The time that it renders a scanline is key: currently I do this 60 PPU clocks from the beginning of a line. It uses the catch-up method, so other aspects of PPU emulation are precise, like the time of H-blank. It's definitely a workable method.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


